<h2>Main Page</h2>
<p>The main page of our application provides direct access to
<ul>
<li>UTA Home page</li>
<li>My Mav</li>
<li>Student Email</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
It allows the users to choose any of the following options 
<ul>
<li><b>Register:</b> It allows a student to create an account with the student email id.</li>

<li><b>Login:</b>It allows students, advisors and admins to login to their accounts.</li>

<li><b>Change password:</b> Any user that is a student, an advisor or an admin can change the password at any time.</li>
<li><b>search:</b> It allows the users to search for any links within the website.</li>
</ul>
<p>The main page also provides the link to various departments to schedule an appointment with that particular department advisor. </p>
<ul>
<li>Bio Engineering</li>
<li>Civil Engineering</li>
<li>Computer Science and Engineering</li>
<li>Electrical Engineering</li>
<li>Industrial Manufacturing and Systems Engineering</li>
<li>Material Science and Engineering</li>

</ul>
<p>The Users can also provide feedback and report any issues or bugs through the respective links provided on the home page.
</p>
<h2>Student Login</h2>
<p>When a student logins to his account, the main page that dispays the current time of the university is displayed. He has the provision to choose two options</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Advising:</b>It allows the student to book an appointment with the advisor based on the type of advising.</li>
<li><b>Appointments:</b> It displays a calendar that shows the appointments of that particular student.</li>
</ul>
When a student choses a advising option, he is navigated to a page which shows a drop down list with following options.
<ul>
<li>Add Class</li>
<li>Drop Class</li>
<li>Transfer Student</li>
</ul>
Based on the type of adivising a student choses, the available slots will be displayed to him. When he clicks on any available slot, a pop up window of <b>"add appointment"</b> appears on the screen. He needs to enter his email ID, UTA student ID, the reason to book an appointment and submit.
<h2>Advisor Login</h2>
<p>When an Advisor logins, the main page that displays the current time of the university is displayed.The advisor is provided with following options.</P>
<ul>
<li><b>Update Schedule:</b>It allows the advisor to add or delete the available time slots.</li>
<li><b>Appointments:</b>It diaplays the calendar that shows the appointments of all advisors.</li>
<li><b>Show Schedule:</b>It displays the calendar that shows the appointments of that particular advisor.</li>
<li><b>Customise Settings:</b>Advisors are allowed to create slots based on their availabilty.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Admin login</h2>
<p>When an admin logins to his account,the main page that displays the current time of the university is displayed. The admin is provided with following options.</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Add New Advisor:</b>It allows the admin to add new advisors.</li>
<li><b>Delete Advisor:</b>It allows the admin to delete any existing advisor</li>
<li><b>Edit Advisor:</b>It allows the admin to change the details of a particular adviosr.</li>
<li><b>Manage User Type:</b>It allows the admin to change the roles of the users.</li>
<li><b>Show Department Schedule:</b>It shows the details of all the appointments. </li>
</ul>
